
[1]chlorite

   CHLORITE, n. A mineral of a grass green color, opake, usually friable
   or easily pulverized, composed of little spangles, scales, prisms or
   shining small grains. It is classed by Kirwan with the muriatic genus.
   There are four subspecies, chlorite earth, common chlorite, chlorite
   slate, and foliated chlorite.
